<HEADLINE>
<P>
PALIMONY CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re "For Richer or for Poorer," by Marlene Adler Marks, Commentary, June 1:  
</P>
<P>
 After years of incorrectly reporting the ultimate result of the Marvin vs. 
Marvin case, your newspaper, in recent years, has acknowledged that "the 
$104,000 finally granted (Michelle Triola)" was actually taken away from her by 
the California Court of Appeal, and that both the California Supreme Court and 
the U.S. Supreme Court refused to overturn that decision. In fact, the only 
monetary award that finally arose out of the case was an award of costs to Lee 
Marvin in the amount of several thousand dollars, which he graciously declined 
to enforce. 
</P>
<P>
 CHARLES D. MEYER 
