<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: A WEEK TO REMEMBER FOR FRESHWATER CATCHES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Southern California and the Eastern Sierra offered something for everyone in 
freshwater fishing last week. 
</P>
<P>
 The San Diego City lakes weighed in with six largemouth bass, from 10 pounds 9 
ounces to 14-7 at Otay, and a 42-pound 3-ounce blue catfish -- largest of the 
year -- at San Vicente. 
</P>
<P>
 Posing for a picture, 5-year-old Jonathan Murata of Rosamond strained to hold 
the 5 1/2-pound rainbow trout he caught at Convict Lake, and veteran bass 
expert Bob Crupi drew attention by taking an 11 1/4-pound largemouth while 
"field testing" a new plastic lure at Castaic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
