WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; OUTREACH PROGRAM RECEIVES $248,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Oxnard Elementary School District has become the first organization in the 
state to receive reimbursement for a Medi-Cal outreach program, said John 
Fitzgerald, the district's director of budget and finance. 
</P>
<P>
 The $248,000 reimbursement was for services provided between July and 
December, 1993. The money will be used to hire a nurse and a psychologist, 
Fitzgerald said. 
</P>
<P>
 Since 1991, the district has had only one nurse, who provides services to 
nearly 13,000 students, Fitzgerald said. The district has six psychologists. 
