<HEADLINE>
<P>
COBI'S OFFSIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "Cobi's Offside," a cartoon that takes both an educational and fun look at 
soccer, begins today.The author and illustrator, Desmond Armstrong, was a 
member of the 1990 U.S. World Cup team as well as the 1988 Olympic soccer team 
that played in Seoul. Armstrong, considered one of the most versatile U.S. 
players ever, was also the first American to play professionally in Brazil. He 
is currently a member of the U.S. Soccer Federation board of directors and will 
serve as a broadcast analyst for this year's World Cup. The character that 
serves as a model for the strip is Cobi Jones, a current member of the U.S. 
team. 
</P>
