<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOP SENIORS IN SOFTBALL ALL-STAR GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The county's best high school seniors will meet tonight at Brea-Olinda High 
School for the third Orange County North-South all-star softball game, 
sponsored by Soroptimist International of Brea. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge Coach Alan Dugard will direct the South, headed by outfielder 
Alison Johnsen, the county's leading hitter and the Southern Section's all-time 
leading base-stealer, and Mater Dei's Candace Kollen and Huntington Beach's 
Stefanie Noffsinger. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon Coach Lance Eddy heads the North team, which will feature shortstop 
Nina Lindenberg as well as Los Alamitos' Debbie and Carolyn Wilson, and 
Orange's Chris Puccio. 
</P>
<P>
 The South won last year, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
 Gates open at 6 p.m. First pitch is at 7 p.m. Tickets are $5 for adults and $3 
for minors. MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
