<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: GIRLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dolores Tuimoloau 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Channel Islands 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Track and field 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Tuimoloau has been the dominant shotputter in the state 
since the start of the season. She opened her outdoor campaign with a 
then-personal best of 45 feet 6 inches to win the Spartan Relays on March 5 and 
moved into a tie for seventh on the all-time state list when she unleashed a 
49-2 effort in the Ventura County championships on April 29.She suffered only 
one defeat this season. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Tuimoloau won the state championships at Cerritos College on 
Saturday with a put of 46-10 to become Channel Islands' first state champion. 
After producing the second-best put (49-0 1/2) of her career in Friday's 
preliminaries, Tuimoloau had the top four marks in the finals. "This is a dream 
come true," Tuimoloau said. "I never imagined winning state when the season 
started. I just wanted to see how much I could improve on my previous marks." 
</P>
</TEXT>
