<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Randy Wolf 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: El Camino Real 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Baseball 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Wolf pitched the Conquistadores to their second 
consecutive City Section 4-A championship, the first time since 1979 that a 
team has won two straight titles. Wolf was 12-3 with a 1.09 earned-run average 
and 133 strikeouts in 129 innings this year.The left-hander, who has signed 
with Pepperdine, was last season's City player of the year and could win the 
award again. In the four playoff games, Wolf earned three victories and a save. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Wolf earned two victories and a save as El Camino Real raced 
to the title. He pitched a one-hitter against Carson in a quarterfinal game 
last Wednesday, saved Friday's semifinal against Kennedy, and pitched all nine 
innings in Monday's 7-6 championship victory against Chatsworth. The 
Chancellors exploded for five runs -- two earned -- against Wolf in the seventh 
inning, but he remained in the game and escaped a jam in the ninth, when he 
retired three consecutive batters with none out and a runner on second base. 
Wolf also was selected Friday by the Dodgers in the 25th round of the major 
league draft. 
</P>
</TEXT>
