<HEADLINE>
<P>
PALESTINIAN TV AIRS IN JERICHO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Palestinian TV completed its first day of broadcasts Tuesday, beaming a test 
pattern that did not reach much beyond the hotel room where it originated. 
</P>
<P>
 But it would have been a contender in the ratings sweepstakes in the five-mile 
radius from Hisham's Palace Hotel.Children sat watching the red, black, green 
and white colors of the Palestinian flag, plus the words Palestinian 
Broadcasting Corporation, fade in and out. 
</P>
<P>
 The fledgling Palestinian effort -- which also includes a few newspapers and 
plans to set up radio broadcasts -- is part of the changes seen as crucial to 
convincing the public that the limited autonomy deal will lead to real 
independence from Israel. 
</P>
<P>
 Newspaper journalist Abdallah abu Sayyam said he doesn't mind the modest 
beginnings because he no longer has to submit copy to Israel's military censor. 
</P>
