<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA HILLS; FREE CLASSES TO HELP THOSE RAISING TEENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two free lectures aimed at helping the parents of teen-agers are scheduled 
this month at the Laguna Hills Hospital and Mental Health Center. 
</P>
<P>
 On Thursday at 7 p.m., Jan Tanner will present "What to Do With a Bored 
Teen-ager." She will address why teen-agers become dissatisfied and how parents 
can develop esteem-boosting activities to make their teens' summer enjoyable. 
</P>
<P>
 Tanner also will give a talk on "How to Raise a Teen-age Rebel" on June 23 at 
7 p.m. She will look at the roots of teen-agers' rebelliousness and how parents 
can get their teen-agers to talk to them. 
</P>
<P>
 The hospital is at 24552 Pacific Park Drive. To make reservations, call 
831-1800, Ext. 268. LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
