</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 American Matches Some TWA Discounts: AMR Corp., parent of American Airlines, 
said it is matching some European fare discounts initiated by Trans World 
Airlines. "We are going to do a limited match of the special on competitive 
routes," a spokesman said.TWA announced the discounts Monday; some carriers 
matched the fares, but others said they were still studying the move because 
European bookings were already strong. The latest discounts allow as much as 
$200 off round-trip tickets purchased by June 13. The lower rates apply to 
travel between July 3 and Aug. 31, with a maximum stay of 30 days. Northwest 
Airlines and United Airlines said they were matching the TWA fares on competing 
routes. Delta Air Lines did not immediately go along. 
