<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: ECONOMY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mid-Sized Manufacturers Expect Growth: About 63% of them plan to add full-time 
employees this year to handle an increasing volume of orders.According to the 
Grant Thornton Survey of American Manufacturers, 65% of the executives 
interviewed last month said they expect to see demand rising for the rest of 
the year. Interviewers surveyed 250 top executives at companies with annual 
sales of between $10 million and $500 million. Among the findings: 49% are 
increasing overtime, 42% are hiring extra part-timers and 42% are using workers 
from temporary agencies for production jobs. Nearly two-thirds of the 
executives said they expect their companies to make more money this year than 
last. 
</P>
</TEXT>
