<TEXT>
<P>
 Orange County Register Halts Ad Campaign: The newspaper agreed to call off the 
countywide campaign because of a trademark dispute with the Washington Post, an 
attorney for the Post said."We're clarifying a few final things, but they have 
agreed to stop using" the phrase, "If you don't get it, you don't get it," said 
Mary Ann Werner, assistant counsel to the Washington newspaper. She added that 
the resolution had been amicable. Register officials said that any agreement is 
still in progress. "I can't comment until I see the response to our 
correspondence" with the Post, said John Schueler, executive vice president and 
general manager of the Register. The Post filed for trademark rights to the 
phrase last fall. 
</P>
