<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; LINKS SERVICE GROUP AWARDS SCHOLARSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Students from colleges and high schools across the county received 
scholarships recently from the local chapter of Links, a national service 
organization. 
</P>
<P>
 The scholarships, which ranged in size from $300 to $750, went mostly to 
African American students, said Laura Rycraw, who heads Links' scholarship 
committee. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is to help out with their educations. The need is there," said Rycraw. 
"Sometimes, the (scholarship money) starts an education. Sometimes, it helps 
people continue their education." 
</P>
<P>
 Scholarship recipients from Cal State Fullerton are: Daniele Fagins of La 
Palma; Ebony Hill of Anaheim and Jennifer Ryan of Brea. Winners from UC Irvine 
are: Taliva Martin of Irvine, Allyce Edwards of Irvine, Denise Hart of Santa 
Ana, Yonnine Hawkins of Los Angeles and Tangye Watson of Carson. 
</P>
<P>
 Recipients from Rancho Santiago College are: Christine Battle of Lake Forest, 
Raymond Comer of Garden Grove, Deloise Moore of Anaheim, Scott Snyder of Tustin 
and Pearline Bedford of Tustin. Biola University student Stephanie Ball also 
won a scholarship.  
</P>
<P>
 Winners from local high schools are: Danine Dias of Fullerton Union High 
School, Christopher Payne of Sunny Hills High School, Renee Poole of Anaheim 
High School and Thomas Tape of Esperanza High School. 
</P>
<P>
 The recipients were honored at a reception last month. 
</P>
<P>
 The Orange County chapter of Links helps sponsor a variety of programs, 
including an annual black history events and programs for African American 
artists.SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
