<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; RODEOS TO BENEFIT ANTI-DRUG GROUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cowboys will be roping and steering in San Juan Capistrano this weekend as a 
benefit for Santa Ana's Drug Use Is Life Abuse nonprofit educational 
association. 
</P>
<P>
 Events on Saturday include a rodeo from 2 to 4 p.m. and a dance from 5 to 9 
p.m. at the Creekside Equestrian Center, 28801 San Juan Creek Road. 
</P>
<P>
 Cowboys will gear up again Sunday for a rodeo from 1 to 3 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are $10 for adults and $6 for children under 12 years old if purchased 
in advance and $12 for adults and $7 for kids at the gate. The gates open two 
hours before the event for parking. 
</P>
<P>
 The rodeos are courtesy of the San Juan Capistrano Professional Rodeo Cowboy 
Assn. This is the third event the association has offered to benefit Drug Use 
Is Life Abuse. 
</P>
<P>
 Drug Use Is Life Abuse was founded by Orange Cty Sheriff Brad Gates in 1987. 
It is based in Santa Ana and was started as a support group of the Sheriff's 
Advisory Council. LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
