<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; WORK TO LIMIT ACCESS ON BUSHARD STREET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Traffic and parking will be restricted for more than a month on Bushard Street 
between Washington Avenue and Kennedy Way because of street repairs. 
</P>
<P>
 Construction of curbs, gutters, a sidewalk and new asphalt pavement will begin 
June 20 and will continue until the last week of July, said Bill Patapoff, an 
administrative assistant at the Development Services Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Patapoff said that one lane in each direction will be open during 
construction. He said there will be access for residents and business owners in 
the area. Construction hours will be from 7:30 a.m. to 4 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The $62,000 project will complete the street improvements around John Murdy 
Elementary School. 
</P>
<P>
 For additional information, call the city's engineering division at (714) 
741-5178. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</TEXT>
