<HEADLINE>
<P>
EDITOR'S NOTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Although "Doonesbury" creator Garry Trudeau refers to the Catholic church as 
blessing same-sex unions, most, but not all, of the claims of such unions point 
to rituals and practices of Catholics who later came to be identified with the 
Eastern Orthodox Church. Church spokesmen dispute the claims  
</P>
<P>
 Also, Roman Catholic teaching holds that homosexual orientation is not in 
itself sinful, but sexual activity outside a heterosexual marriage is 
considered a sin. 
</P>
