<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: AMERIQUEST TECHNOLOGIES AND KENFIL INC. MAKE STOCK SWAP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AmeriQuest Technologies Inc., a distributor of computer hardware, has traded 
1.1 million newly issued common shares for 3.3 million shares, or 51%, of 
Kenfil Inc. common stock held by its principal shareholders. 
</P>
<P>
 The stock swap, first announced in April, is part of AmeriQuest's proposed 
acquisition of Kenfil, a Van Nuys-based software distributor. 
</P>
<P>
 Subject to the approvals of both companies' shareholders, the remaining Kenfil 
shares would be exchanged in a merger at the same conversion ratio of 0.34 
AmeriQuest shares for each Kenfil common share. The all-stock deal is expected 
to be completed in August. The value of the merger fluctuates with stock prices 
but is estimated to be in the neighborhood of $17 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Simultaneously with the merger, holders of about $7.3 million of Kenfil 
subordinated debt will exchange the debt for additional AmeriQuest common 
shares. 
</P>
