<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE 1994-95 BROADWAY SERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jan Herman 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coming to the Orange County Performing Arts Center: 
</P>
<P>
 * Nov. 29-Dec. 4: "Jelly's Last Jam" by George C. Wolfe with music by Jelly 
Roll Morton and King Oliver and lyrics by Susan Birkenhead. 
</P>
<P>
 * Dec. 27-Jan. 1: "The Sound of Music" with music by Richard Rodgers and 
lyrics by Oscar Hammerstein II. 
</P>
<P>
 * Feb. 7-12: "Blood Brothers" with music and lyrics by Willy Russell. 
</P>
<P>
 * June 6-11, 1995: "Hello, Dolly!" with music and lyrics by Jerry Herman. 
</P>
<P>
 * June 21-25, 1995: "Porgy and Bess" with music by George Gershwin and lyrics 
by Ira Gershwin. 
</P>
<P>
 * July 18-23, 1995: "Joseph and the Amazing Technicolor Dreamcoat" with music 
by Andrew Lloyd Webber and lyrics by Tim Rice. 
</P>
<P>
 Subscriptions go on sale Aug. 8. The center is at 600 Town Center Drive in 
Costa Mesa. (714) 556-2787. Jan Herman 
</P>
</TEXT>
